  The histories also indicate the complexity of the tasks and the
practical difficulties that local school boards face when they seek to
achieve greater racial integration. The boards work in communities where
demographic patterns change, where they must meet traditional learning
goals, where they must attract and retain effective teachers, where
they should (and will) take account of parents’ views and maintain
\\their\\ commitment to public school education, where they must adapt
to court intervention, where they must encourage voluntary student and
