175 S. E. 2d 649, 650– 651 (1970). This Court upheld the plan, see
\\McDaniel,\\ 402 U. S., at 41, rejecting the parents’ argument that
“a person may not be \\included\\ or \\excluded\\ solely because
he is a Negro or because he is white,” Brief for Respondents in
\\McDaniel,\\ O. T. 1970, No. 420, p. 25.

  Federal authorities had claimed—as the NAACP and the OCR did in
